# React / Next.js Component Patterns

## Server vs Client Components

- Server Components are the **default**. Keep data fetching and heavy logic in them.
- Add `"use client"` only when the component needs: event handlers, hooks, or browser APIs.
- Never fetch data inside a Client Component — pass it down as props from a Server Component.

```tsx
// ✅ Server Component (default — no directive needed)
interface TeamMembersTableProps {
  organizationId: string;
}

export default async function TeamMembersTable({
  organizationId,
}: TeamMembersTableProps) {
  const members = await getTeamMembers(organizationId);
  return <div className="p-4">{members.length} members</div>;
}

// ✅ Client Component (only when necessary)
"use client";
export function ClockInButton({ canClockIn }: { canClockIn: boolean }) {
  const [pending, setPending] = useState(false);
  return <button onClick={() => setPending(true)}>{canClockIn ? "Clock in" : "Unavailable"}</button>;
}
```

## Props

- Always define an explicit `interface` for props — never inline complex types.
- Name it `<ComponentName>Props`.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
export function Card({ title, count }: { title: string; count: number }) {}

// ✅ GOOD
interface CardProps {
  title: string;
  count: number;
}
export function Card({ title, count }: CardProps) {}
```

## Styling — TailwindCSS v4

- TailwindCSS v4 uses a CSS-first config (`@theme` in `globals.css`) — no `tailwind.config.js`.
- Use Tailwind utility classes only. No inline styles, no CSS Modules.
- Use `cn()` (from `@/lib/utils`) to conditionally merge classes.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";
<div className={cn("p-4 rounded-lg", isActive && "bg-primary text-primary-foreground")} />
```

## UI Components

- Prefer shadcn/ui primitives (`Button`, `Input`, `Card`, `Dialog`, etc.) over custom HTML.
- Only build a custom component when shadcn/ui doesn't cover the use case.
- For dense ops screens, prioritize legibility: tables, cards, badges, tabs, and empty states over decorative UI.

## File Placement

- Shared components → `src/components/<name>.tsx`
- Page-specific components → `src/app/<route>/_components/<name>.tsx`
- One component per file; filename matches the exported function name.
